t the method is applicable to a variety of\ndifferent materials beyond the conductor, and term our instrument a scanning\nnoise microscope (SNoiM):In general non-equilibrium current fluctuations are\ngenerated in any materials including dielectrics, metals and molecular systems.\nThe fluctuations, in turn, excite fluctuating electric and magnetic evanescent\nfields on the material surface, which can be detected and imaged by our SNoiM.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 6 Oct 2016 01:53:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 7 Oct 2016 12:14:43 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 23 Oct 2016 15:20:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-05-22"}
